Company Overview of HGK Asset Management, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
HGK Asset Management, Inc. is an employee owned investment manager. It primarily provides its services to other pooled investment vehicles. The firm also caters to individuals, high net worth individuals, investment companies, charitable organizations, corporations, and State or municipal government entities. It manages separate client-focused equity and fixed income portfolios. The firm also launches and manages equity mutual funds for its clients. It invests in the public equity, fixed income, and alternative investments markets across the globe. The firm primarily makes its alternative investments in private debt instruments and supplemental fixed income strategies. It primarily invests i...
HGK Asset Management, Inc. is an employee owned investment manager. It primarily provides its services to other pooled investment vehicles. The firm also caters to individuals, high net worth individuals, investment companies, charitable organizations, corporations, and State or municipal government entities. It manages separate client-focused equity and fixed income portfolios. The firm also launches and manages equity mutual funds for its clients. It invests in the public equity, fixed income, and alternative investments markets across the globe. The firm primarily makes its alternative investments in private debt instruments and supplemental fixed income strategies. It primarily invests in value stocks of companies across all capitalizations and core stocks of large cap companies. The firm employs a fundamental and a quantitative analysis along with bottom-up stock picking approach to create its portfolio. For its fixed income securities, the firm invests in treasury, agency, corporate, mortgage backed securities, and asset backed securities. It benchmarks the performance of its fixed income portfolios against Barclays Capital Government/Credit Index and Merrill Lynch 1 - 3 Year Domestic Master. The firm also employs a conservative approach to make its investments. HGK Asset Management was founded in June 1983 and is based in Jersey City, New Jersey with an additional office in Southport, Connecticut.
