HGK Asset Management | Creating Value For Our Clients






































 




















Consistent and Disciplined 
Philosophy
People
Process
Principles
 






Creating Value For Our Clients Since 1983

HGK Asset Management is an independent registered Investment Advisor located in Jersey City, New Jersey. Founded in 1983, HGK is 100% employee owned with portfolio managers averaging over 20 years of investment experience and 15 years tenure with the firm.
HGK manages over $2.5 billion for more than 200 clients worldwide. The firm seeks to add value for clients by investing in undervalued securities in all of its investment disciplines.






Core Principles

Employee owned
Experienced professionals
Home grown investment team
Analytical, idea driven culture
Enduring client partnerships
Long term focus
 


























Operations Archives - HGK Asset Management
































 

















Our Team








Operations






David C. Hauck, CPA Managing Partner  Chief Financial Officer  Chief Compliance Officer









David C. Hauck, CPA Managing Partner  Chief Financial Officer  Chief Compliance Officer

David Hauck is a Managing Partner, serving as HGK’s Chief Financial Officer and Chief Compliance Officer. He is responsible for managing the administrative, financial, and compliance operations at the Firm. Dave has been with HGK since 1999 and has more than 32 years of investment experience. Prior to joining HGK, he held senior institutional sales positions at Donaldson Lufkin & Jenrette, Kidder Peabody, L.F. Rothschild, and Prudential Bache; additionally, Dave was an Audit Supervisor at Touche Ross.
David earned a Bachelor of Science in Accounting from C.W. Post College. He earned his Certified Public Accountant designation in 1981. Dave is a member of HGK’s Board of Directors.









JoAnn Conry Vice President  Operations 









JoAnn Conry Vice President  Operations 

JoAnn Conry is Vice President of Operations. JoAnn manages the back office operations department, overseeing trade settlements, account reconciliations, and client reporting.
She has been with the Firm since 1988.









Brandon Slywka IT Manager









Brandon Slywka IT Manager

Brandon Slywka is HGK’s Information Technology Manager. Brandon is responsible for the implementation, support, and maintenance of all of the Firm’s Information Technology Infrastructure. He has been with the Firm since 2010; for five years prior to this, Brandon was performing IT consulting for HGK through a third-party computer services firm. Brandon gained experience in network troubleshooting and implementation while working for various computer services firms and complex contract based projects.
Brandon has earned CompTIA A+ , Network +, VMware VCP and Microsoft MCSE Server 2012 certifications. He is currently working towards his Security + and CISSP certifications.









